"{\n    \"Title\": \"Notes to the Consolidated Financial StatementsFor the year ended March 31, 2020\",\n    \"row 1\": \"2. Significant accounting policies (Continued from previous page)\",\n    \"row 2\": \"Measurement uncertainty\",\n    \"row 3\": \"The preparation of consolidated financial statements in conformity with Canadian public sector accounting standards\",\n    \"row 4\": \"requires management to make estimates and assumptions that affect the reported amounts of assets and liabilities, and\",\n    \"row 5\": \"disclosure of contingent assets and liabilities, at the date of the consolidated financial statements, and the reported\",\n    \"row 6\": \"amounts of revenue and expenses during the reporting period.\",\n    \"row 7\": \"Accounts receivable are stated after evaluation as to their collectability and an appropriate allowance for doubtful accounts\",\n    \"row 8\": \"is provided where considered necessary.\",\n    \"row 9\": \"Amortization is based on the estimated useful lives of tangible capital assets.\",\n    \"row 10\": \"Accounts payable and accruals are estimated based on historical charges for unbilled goods and services at year-end.\",\n    \"row 11\": \"Deferred revenue is estimated based on management's review of revenue received, but unspent at year-end.\",\n    \"row 12\": \"Inventory for resale\",\n    \"row 13\": \"Inventory for resale is valued at the lower of cost and net realizable value. Cost is determined by the first-in, first-out\",\n    \"row 14\": \"method. Net realizable value is the estimated selling price in the ordinary course of business, less estimated costs of\",\n    \"row 15\": \"completion and selling costs.\",\n    \"row 16\": \"Segments\",\n    \"row 17\": \"The First Nation conducts its business through eleven reportable segments. These operating segments are established by\",\n    \"row 18\": \"senior management to facilitate the achievement of the First Nation's long-term objectives to aid in resource allocation\",\n    \"row 19\": \"decisions, and to assess operational performance.\",\n    \"row 20\": \"For each reported segment, revenue and expenses represent both amounts that are directly attributable to the segment and\",\n    \"row 21\": \"amounts that are allocated on a reasonable basis. Therefore, certain allocation methodologies are employed in the\",\n    \"row 22\": \"preparation of segmented financial information.\",\n    \"row 23\": \"The accounting policies used in these segments are consistent with those followed in the preparation of the consolidated\",\n    \"row 24\": \"financial statements as disclosed in Note 2 Significant accounting policies.\",\n    \"row 25\": \"Employee future benefits\",\n    \"row 26\": \"The First Nation's employee future benefit program consists of a defined contribution plan. The First Nation contributions to\",\n    \"row 27\": \"the defined contribution plan are expensed as incurred.\"\n}"